-- MOVES-Castle Harbour hires ex-Citigroup executive Eric Daniel
-- By Yashaswini Swamynathan in Bengaluru
-- Wed Dec 10, 2014 11:52AM EST
-- None



Dec 10 (Reuters) - Financial services provider Castle Harbour Securities appointed former Citigroup Inc <C.N> executive Eric Daniel to co-manage its new global convertible bond fund.

Daniel was most recently the head of equity derivatives and convertible bond sales at Citigroup's Paris office. He will run the Castle Harbour R&D - Pure Global Convertibles Fund with Damien Regnier.